# Trivy CVE suppressions for the runtime image scan in .github/workflows/release.yml.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line; lines starting with `#` are comments.
# trivy-action picks this file up from the workspace root automatically.
#
# Each entry MUST cite:
#   - the package the CVE lives in,
#   - why it is unreachable from the coxswain binary,
#   - the issue tracking the entry's eventual removal.
# Stop-gap entries belong here; durable fixes belong in the Dockerfile.

# CVE-2026-45447 — HIGH — libssl3 3.0.20-1~deb12u1 (Debian bookworm)
# Use-after-free in OpenSSL's PKCS7_verify() with a crafted empty-set
# digestAlgorithms field. Lives in libssl3.so.3, bundled by
# gcr.io/distroless/cc-debian12:nonroot as part of the cc-runtime package set.
#
# Unreachable from the coxswain binary: verified via
#   readelf -d /usr/local/bin/coxswain
# on the published image; the only NEEDED entries are libc.so.6, libgcc_s.so.1,
# and libm.so.6. Pingora's boring-sys statically links BoringSSL into the
# binary, so the OpenSSL PKCS#7 code path is not in the process address space —
# nothing in coxswain's call graph loads or calls into libssl3.so.3.
#
# Fixed upstream in Debian's libssl3 3.0.20-1~deb12u2; the suppression becomes
# inactive when Google ships a distroless/cc-debian12 image carrying that
# package (the mutable :nonroot tag means subsequent builds pull the fix).
#
# Tracking the durable fix (remove libssl3 from the runtime image entirely):
# coxswain-labs/coxswain#228.
# Tracking this suppression entry: coxswain-labs/coxswain#227.
CVE-2026-45447
